<plot>In "Pawns of the King," a former WWII Japanese Imperial Navy pilot, who's haunted by the past, is forced to confront his fears when he meets an old enemy, a U.S. Army 442nd Regimental Combat Team soldier, and plays a fateful game of chess. Japanese Imperial Navy pilots are legendary for their battles in the Pacific War. The U.S. Army 442nd Regimental Combat Team is the most decorated unit in U.S. military history and composed almost entirely of Japanese Americans.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?426799</url></doc>
